{"lemma":"أَكْيَسِ","slug":"أَكْيَسِ","root":"ك.#.س","root_slug":"ك-_-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-_-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37399","n37407"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of كَيِّس (kayyis, “cunning, acute, sharp-witted, shrewd”)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring forth clever children"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37399","headword_ar":"اَكْيَسَ","root":"kys","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had born to him children acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick in intellect; shrewd; clever, ingenious, skilful, knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he begot a child acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (IKtt.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyasato","text_ar":"اَكْيَسَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAsato","text_ar":"اَكَاسَتْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She brought forth children acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (A.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falawo kunotumo limikoyasapK A^akaAsato\n                      \n                     \n                        wakayosu AlA^um~i yuEorafu fiY AlbaniynaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But if ye belonged to one who most generally brought forth children acute in intellect, she had brought forth such children; for the acuteness of intellect of the mother is known in the sons"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n37407","headword_ar":"اَكْيَسٌ","root":"kys","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick in intellect; more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, shrewd, clever, ingenious, skilful, knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Lth, ISd, A:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiysaY","text_ar":"كِيسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, ISd:) [in the CK, and in a MS. copy of the K, and in the text of the K as given in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiysaY","text_ar":"كِيسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", each of which is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuyosaY","text_ar":"كُيْسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", are said to be fems. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowasu","text_ar":"اَكْوَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is evidently a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyasu","text_ar":"اَكْيَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsN","text_ar":"كُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuyosN","text_ar":"كُيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] which is applied to women, [as well as men,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsayaAtN","text_ar":"كُوسَيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied to women only. (Lth.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^akoyasu","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَكْيَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Lth.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u Almuw^ominiyna A^akoyasu","text_ar":"اَىُّ المُوْمِنِينَ اَكْيَسُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Which of the believers is the most intelligent?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said in a proverb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyasu mino qi$~apK","text_ar":"اَكْيَسُ مِنْ قِشَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) [(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little female ape"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"monkey."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q$","text_ar":"قش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyasu Alkayosi Alt~uqaY","text_ar":"اَكْيَسُ الكَيْسِ التُّقَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^aHomaqu AlHumoqi Alfujuwru","text_ar":"وَاَحْمَقُ الحُمْقِ الفُجُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most acute of acuteness is piety, and the most foolish of foolishness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most stupid of stupidness, is vice"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isN","text_ar":"كَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Lth","ISd","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}